function getThreeCharacterCode(filename) {
  const regex = /^(\d+)-([A-Za-z0-9]{3})\.usfm$/;
  const match = regex.exec(filename);
  if (match !== null) {
    return match[2];
  } else {
    return null;
  }
}
```
You can use this function to extract the three character code from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm". The regex pattern `/^(\d+)-([A-Za-z0-9]{3})\.usfm$/` matches the following:

* `^`: Start of string
* `\d+`: One or more digits
* `-`: A hyphen
* `[A-Za-z0-9]{3}`: Three characters that are either upper or lower case letters or digits
* `\.usfm`: The `.usfm` file extension
* `$`: End of string

The function uses the `exec()` method to execute the regex pattern against the input filename, and returns the third capture group (the three character code) if a match is found. If no match is found, it returns null.
